Turkey summons US diplomat over spy report
Turkey's Foreign Ministry has summoned the country's most senior American diplomat to comment on a report of American and British spying in Turkey.
Deputy Prime Minister Bulent said that the US attorney general and Turkish officials discussed the message on Monday.
German magazine Der Spiegel and online magazine The Intercept reported that documents provided by former US National Security Agency analyst Edward Snowden show that Turkey was a priority target for US and British intelligence services.
According to Turkish news agency, Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan downplayed the significance of the report, saying that all major countries are spying on each other.
