I took these pictures at a family holiday using several cameras, all for about $350.
Regardless of the equipment you use, there are a few rules to follow in order to get the best results.
Check your equipment again.
Even if you have a waterproof camera, make sure that the battery cell and other compartments are tightly closed.
Also, set your camera for the type of photos or videos you will be taking.
Some cameras have shooting modes or object types that optimize exposure for dim underwater conditions.
And before you jump in, you have to figure out how deep your equipment can go.
