For most cancers, it's difficult to pinpoint the exact cause.
Although some smokers develop lung cancer, for example, not all lung cancer patients are smokers.
But mesothelioma is different.
In almost all cases, the cause is asbestos, a fibrous building material once called "a miracle" but now known to be deadly.
For most of us, mesothelioma is a disease that can be ignored.
Asbestos, after all, is a thing of the past.
The most dangerous type of asbestos has not been used in the UK since the 1960s, when the recommended industrial ban came into force.
Even when it was used, only people in specific industries worked in close contact with it: pipe insulators, builders, carpenters and dock workers, for example.
An industrial toxin from another era, it's hardly a cause for concern today.
