The reason we're feeling its deadly effects now is that although the use of asbestos has been illegal for many years (all types of asbestos were eventually outlawed in 1999), it usually takes tens of years for mesothelioma to develop.
And mesothelioma is not limited to veterans of industrial construction.
Asbestos has been, and in many cases remains, in the homes where we live, the offices where we work, the schools where we study, and the stores where we shop.
As a result, mesothelioma does not care about class, wealth, profession or age.
The bastions of the elite, from the fashionable London department stores to the private schools, have not been the salvation.
The parliament building is riddled with asbestos.
