We are talking about only those cases where the accident was registered according to the "Euro protocol" without the participation of the traffic police.
So if there were only two cars involved in the accident, no physical injuries, the damage is within the limit, and both drivers have reached an agreement as to who is to blame for the accident.
From August 2, the payment limit under the "euro protocol" will be 50 thousand rubles, and from October 1 in Moscow, St. Petersburg, as well as in Moscow and Leningrad regions, it will be increased to 400 thousand rubles.
