Because if you had a policy, you couldn't get a refund without a GIBD certificate.
The parameters set out in the draft directive are precisely intended to remove this obstacle to the implementation of the "euro protocol" in Russia.
According to them, the maximum payment for a casco in connection with an accident, filed without the GIBDD employees, should not be lower than the limit under the "euro protocol".
But it cannot be higher than the limit specified in the casco insurance contract.
The idea is certainly useful and theoretically capable of relieving both the employees of the DPS and the road.
